You are a senior creative technologist and UI engineer. Build a complete, production-ready, multi-page **marketing website** for a corporate document management platform called **CMR DMS / DocAI**. The website must be deliverable as a static folder — no build step, no server-side runtime, no package manager. A user must be able to drop the folder on any standard web host or local server and browse it immediately.

---

## PLATFORM CONTEXT

**CMR DMS / DocAI** is an enterprise **Document Management System** designed for corporations, government agencies, legal firms, and compliance-heavy organizations. It helps teams:

- Upload, organize, search, and track documents centrally across category hierarchies. [Manual §2, §5]
- Control who can view, edit, download, or sign each file — down to individual page-level permissions. [Manual §4]
- Automate multi-step approval workflows with graphical progress tracking. [Manual §11]
- Monitor every document action through a searchable, sortable audit trail. [Manual §14]
- Collect documents from external users without requiring them to have an account. [Manual §8]
- Use AI to generate, summarize, deep-search inside, and template documents. [Manual §12]
- Apply digital signatures and text watermarks to PDFs natively. [Manual §7]
- Set recurring reminders tied to documents or events with in-app and email delivery. [Manual §10]
- Manage a directory of clients alongside internal users. [Manual §4]
- Operate the interface in multiple languages for global teams. [Manual §3]
- White-label the platform with the organization's own branding and logo. [Manual §3]

The **target market** is mid-to-large enterprises, compliance officers, legal departments, HR teams, and IT administrators who value **precision, security, and control**. The tone is: authoritative, modern, trustworthy — not playful.

---

## AESTHETIC DIRECTION

**Theme**: Precision-Futurism. Think the intersection of a Bloomberg Terminal and a high-end architecture firm's pitch deck. Dark background, deep navy to near-black. Sharp typographic hierarchy. Controlled use of accent color — a clean electric teal (`#00C9B1`) or cold blue-white — used sparingly as a highlight, never as a flood fill. Grid-based, structured, but broken deliberately by one or two bold artistic elements.

**Mood board concepts to internalize**:
- CERN / scientific instrument dashboards
- Satellite imagery HUDs
- High-altitude aerospace interfaces
- Architecture blueprints redrawn in light

**Typography**:
- Display/headline font: `"DM Serif Display"` (from Google Fonts) — gives gravitas and a slight editorial edge.
- Body/UI font: `"IBM Plex Mono"` for labels and metadata details, `"DM Sans"` for readable body text.
- Load all from Google Fonts CDN. No fallback to system fonts for display text.

**Color palette**:
```
--bg-deep:        #07090F   /* near-black, primary background */
--bg-surface:     #0D1117   /* card/panel surfaces */
--bg-elevated:    #141B24   /* elevated panels, nav */
--accent:         #00C9B1   /* teal accent — headlines, glows, CTAs */
--accent-cold:    #4F9CF9   /* cold blue for secondary highlights */
--text-primary:   #E8ECF4   /* main body text */
--text-secondary: #7A8599   /* subtext, labels */
--border:         #1E2A38   /* subtle borders */
--danger:         #F04A4A   /* never used decoratively */
```

**DO NOT** use purple gradients, white backgrounds, Inter or Roboto fonts, generic card grids with rounded corners and shadows, or any visual pattern that screams "SaaS landing page template."

---

## TECH STACK REQUIREMENTS

- **Pure HTML5 + CSS3 + Vanilla JavaScript**. No framework, no bundler, no npm.
- **Three.js** loaded via CDN (`https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/three.js/r128/three.min.js`). No OrbitControls or other add-ons that require module imports.
- All other libraries (GSAP, etc.) loaded via CDN if used.
- **File structure** (create every file listed):

```
