### `index.html` — Homepage

**Section 1: Hero** [Manual §1 Quick Start, §2 Introduction]
- Full-viewport height section. Three.js canvas is the background.
- Centered layout.
- Eyebrow label: `ENTERPRISE DOCUMENT INTELLIGENCE` in IBM Plex Mono, spaced uppercase, small, teal.
- H1: `Control Every Document. Automate Every Process.` — in DM Serif Display, very large (clamp 48px → 96px). Line-break after "Document." for dramatic effect.
- Subheadline: `CMR DMS / DocAI gives compliance-driven organizations a single, intelligent system to manage documents, enforce protocols, and maintain a complete audit trail — with no manual overhead.`
- Two CTA buttons: "Request a Demo" (solid accent) and "Explore the Platform" (ghost).
- Below the buttons: a horizontal row of 5 trust badges in IBM Plex Mono micro-text:
  `256-bit Encryption` / `Full Audit Trail` / `Role-Based Access` / `AI-Assisted` / `Multi-Language`
- Below the fold: `assets/hero-dashboard.png` in a perspective-tilted container (CSS `transform: perspective(1200px) rotateX(8deg)`) with a subtle teal glow underneath. Placeholder if image missing.

**Section 2: The Problem** [Manual §2 Introduction]
- Full-width section, dark surface.
- Left half: Large italic pull quote in DM Serif Display — *"Most enterprise document failures aren't technical. They're structural. The wrong version, in the wrong hands, at the wrong time."*
- Right half: 4 short problem statements:
  - `Documents scattered across email threads and shared drives.`
  - `No visibility into who accessed, edited, approved — or when.`
  - `Manual approval chains that collapse under compliance pressure.`
  - `External stakeholders sharing files through untracked channels.`

**Section 3: Platform Overview** [Manual §2, §4–§15 — all feature modules]
- Eyebrow: `THE PLATFORM`
- H2: `One system. Every document. Complete control.`
- 8 feature cards in a CSS Grid (4×2 on desktop, 2×4 on tablet, 1 col on mobile). Each card: icon area (CSS-drawn or Unicode), bold title, two-line description. Cards have a thin `--border` border, hover state lifts with teal edge glow (`box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0,201,177,0.1)`). Features:
  1. **Document Library** [Manual §5] — Centralized repository with category hierarchy, version history, and expiration tracking.
  2. **Workflow Automation** [Manual §11] — Multi-step approvals with visual step graphs and real-time status tracking.
  3. **Role-Based Access** [Manual §4] — Granular permissions by role or individual, down to page-level overrides.
  4. **AI Document Engine** [Manual §12] — Generate documents, summarize existing files, and deep-search inside content.
  5. **Signatures & Watermarks** [Manual §7] — Sign and brand PDFs natively, with every action audited and versioned.
  6. **Audit & Compliance** [Manual §14] — Every action on every document, logged, sortable, and searchable.
  7. **File Requests** [Manual §8] — Collect documents from anyone via a unique link — no account required.
  8. **Reminders & Notifications** [Manual §10] — Recurring alerts tied to documents or deadlines, delivered in-app and by email.

**Section 4: Statistics Bar** [Manual §2, §14, §15]
- Full-width dark band. 4 stats in a row, animated count-up on scroll entry:
  - `100%` — Documents Accounted For
  - `< 2s` — AI Generation Start Time
  - `360°` — Audit Coverage
  - `∞` — Version History Retained
- Numbers large in DM Serif Display, labels small in IBM Plex Mono.

**Section 5: Video Demo Teaser** [Manual §11 Workflows]
- H2: `See the workflow in motion.`
- An `<video autoplay muted loop playsinline>` element pointing to `assets/demo-workflow.mp4`, styled as a screen/monitor mockup. Styled placeholder if file missing.

**Section 6: CTA Banner**
- Full width, subtle teal-to-dark gradient strip.
- H2: `Ready to bring your documents under control?`
- Single button: "Request a Demo"

