### `ai.html` — AI Capabilities [Manual §12, §5]

**Section 1**: Full-viewport hero. H1: `Document Intelligence, Built In.` Subtext: `Generate, summarize, search inside, and template — AI built into the document layer, not bolted on top.` Three.js background with conditional pulsing glow sphere activated only on this page: check `document.body.dataset.page === 'ai'` and add a `PointLight` with color `#00C9B1` and intensity that pulses using `Math.sin(clock)`.

**Section 2**: Four feature cards in a 2×2 grid (2 col desktop, 1 col mobile) [Manual §12]:

- **AI Document Generator** [Manual §12 §AI Document Generator]
  Describe a document in plain language. The system writes it in real time, streaming content directly into a rich text editor. Starts in under 2 seconds. Edit, format, and save without leaving the platform. Every generation event — including the original prompt — is stored and retrievable in the AI Document List.

- **AI Document Summary** [Manual §5 — document action menu, §12]
  Select any document already in your library and generate an instant AI summary. Useful for reviewing lengthy files, onboarding team members, or quickly extracting the key points of a policy or contract without reading the full document.

- **Deep Search** [Manual §9]
  Search inside the content of PDFs, Word documents, Excel spreadsheets, and text files — not just filenames or tags. Case-insensitive, with word stemming (searching "approve" finds "approved," "approving"). Returns the top 10 most relevant results. Common stop words are automatically excluded for precision.

- **Prompt Templates** [Manual §12 §AI Prompt Templates]
  Pre-built prompt structures with named placeholders that fill in on demand. Select a template, enter the variable values, and the system assembles the final prompt automatically. Ideal for documents generated repeatedly — NDAs, privacy notices, policy acknowledgements, onboarding letters.

**Section 3**: `assets/demo-ai.mp4` video demo in a styled dark monitor frame. Placeholder if missing. [Manual §12]

**Section 4**: `assets/feature-ai.png` full-width screenshot with CSS `position: absolute` annotation callouts pointing to:
- The prompt input field
- The streaming output area
- The rich text editor toolbar
- The save/export button
Placeholder layout if image missing — show the four annotation labels in a 2×2 grid. [Manual §12]

**Section 5**: `assets/feature-ai-summary.png` — a second visual showcasing the AI Summary action, shown as a half-width image beside a paragraph explaining the use case. Placeholder if missing. [Manual §5, §12]

**Section 6**: FAQ accordion — 6 questions [Manual §12]:

1. **Is my data sent to OpenAI?**
   Prompts are processed via a secured API call. OpenAI credentials are never exposed to the browser. All prompts and generated outputs are stored securely in your own system — not in any shared or external database.

2. **What file types does Deep Search support?**
   PDF, Word documents (DOCX), Excel spreadsheets (XLSX), and plain text files (TXT). Searching is not case-sensitive and matches word variations automatically.

3. **Can I customize prompt templates?**
   Yes. Administrators can create, edit, and delete prompt templates from the admin panel. Templates support any number of named placeholders.

4. **Does AI generation require internet access?**
   AI document generation and AI summarization require connectivity to the OpenAI API. Deep Search operates entirely on your stored documents and does not require any external connection.

5. **Is every AI generation logged?**
   Yes. Every generation event — including the original prompt — is stored in the AI Document List and is visible to authorized administrators. This makes AI use auditable and accountable.

6. **What happens if the AI fails to generate?**
   The system shows a clear error message. Common causes: blank prompt, network connectivity issue, or OpenAI rate limit. Simply wait a few minutes and retry. All errors are logged for admin visibility.

