### `security.html` — Security & Compliance [Manual §14, §4, §7, §13, §15]

**Section 1**: H1: `Security Without Compromise.` Subheading: `Every permission, every action, every access attempt — tracked, logged, and auditable.`

**Section 2**: `assets/security-diagram.png` full-width with an animated CSS scan-line overlay — a thin horizontal line that sweeps from top to bottom on a 4-second loop using a `@keyframes` animation. Pure CSS. Placeholder if image missing. [Manual §13 Storage Settings]

**Section 3**: 8 security pillars in a 2×4 grid (2 col desktop, 1 col mobile) [Manual §4, §7, §13, §14]:

- **Role-Based Access Control** [Manual §4 Roles] — Permissions defined at role level. Overridable per individual user for page-specific access. Drag-and-drop role assignment with instant inheritance.
- **256-bit Encrypted Storage** [Manual §13 Storage Settings] — Files stored encrypted at rest in AWS S3 or on your local server. Encryption enabled per storage configuration. A test upload verifies the configuration before it is saved.
- **Complete Document Audit Trail** [Manual §14 Document Audit History] — Every read, write, share, delete, signature, watermark, and version restore logged with user and timestamp. Searchable and sortable by any column.
- **Login Audit Logs** [Manual §14 Login Audit Logs] — Every authentication attempt — successful or failed — recorded with username, IP address, date, and time. Identify anomalies and unauthorized access attempts immediately.
- **Time-Bounded Sharing** [Manual §7 Share Document] — All document shares carry optional start and end dates. Access expires automatically. Revoke instantly at any time.
- **Password-Protected External Links** [Manual §7 Shareable Link] — External sharing links can require a password and expire on a set date. Download permission is controlled independently.
- **Digital Signature Integrity** [Manual §7 Digital Signatures] — PDF signatures are encrypted to ensure tamper-proof integrity. Every signature action is versioned and logged in the audit trail.
- **Automated Retention & Cleanup** [Manual §15] — Archive retention policies automatically delete documents after 30, 60, 90, 180, or 365 days. Deletion is executed by a scheduled cron job and logged in the Cron Job Logs.

**Section 4**: Audit & Logging detail — three-column layout [Manual §14]:

- **Document Audit History** — Search by document name, meta tag, or user. Sort by date, operation, category, performed by, directed to user, directed to role. Click any entry to navigate directly to the associated document.
- **Email Logs** — Track every email sent by the system: sender, recipient, subject, body preview, attachments, and delivery status (Sent, Failed, Queued, Delivered, Opened, Bounced). Error details captured if delivery fails.
- **Cron Job Logs** — Visibility into all 12 automated background tasks: daily notification handler, weekly/monthly/quarterly/semi-annual/yearly reminders, archive retention enforcement, log cleanup, and more. Filter by job name, date, and execution status.

**Section 5**: Two-column compliance callout [Manual §2, §14]:
- Left: Large DM Serif Display text — *"Built for organizations where a missing signature, a wrong version, or an unauthorized view is not a workflow inconvenience — it's a liability."*
- Right: Compliance-relevant feature list with teal checkmarks:
  - Full document audit trail with sortable search
  - Login audit logs with IP tracking
  - Time-bounded, revocable access sharing
  - Digital signature with version and audit logging
  - Automated archive retention enforcement (30–365 days)
  - Password-protected external sharing links
  - Encrypted storage with test-verified configuration
  - Workflow logs for every approval and transition

**Section 6**: Automated Background Tasks — a compact table showcasing all 12 cron jobs [Manual §14 Cron Job Logs]:

| Job | Schedule | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Custom Date Reminder | On demand | Sends reminders on user-defined dates |
| Daily Notification Handler | Daily | Aggregates and sends daily document alerts |
| Weekly Reminder | Weekly | Recurring weekly reminders for document actions |
| Monthly Reminder | Monthly | Monthly deadline and review notifications |
| Quarterly Reminder | Every 3 months | Quarterly document review prompts |
| Half Yearly Reminder | Every 6 months | Semi-annual renewal and review alerts |
| Yearly Reminder | Annual | Annual compliance and renewal notifications |
| Notification Scheduler | Continuous | Coordinates all scheduled notification delivery |
| Send Email | Triggered | Processes all queued outgoing emails reliably |
| Delete Archive By Retention Date | Daily | Auto-deletes archived documents past retention |
| Delete/Archive/Expire By Retention | Daily | Applies retention rules: delete, archive, or expire |
| Delete Email, Audit & Cron Logs | Periodic | Cleans up old log records for performance |

Style this table with IBM Plex Mono, alternating row backgrounds using `--bg-surface` and `--bg-elevated`, teal first-column text, and no outer border radius.

