## RESPONSIVENESS REQUIREMENTS

- All layouts must work at 320px minimum width.
- Navigation collapses to hamburger at `< 900px`.
- All CSS Grid layouts must use `auto-fit` / `minmax` or explicit media queries. Never use fixed pixel widths on grid columns.
- Font sizes must use `clamp()` for fluid scaling — no fixed large font sizes that overflow on mobile.
- The Three.js canvas reduces particle count to 30 on mobile and disables mouse parallax.
- Images use `width: 100%; height: auto;` always.
- The perspective-tilted hero dashboard image removes its `transform` on mobile.
- Video elements use `width: 100%; max-width: 960px;` centered.
- The features.html alternating layout switches to single-column stacked (image always above text) on mobile.
- The security page cron jobs table must be horizontally scrollable on mobile (`overflow-x: auto` on a wrapper div).
- Touch targets (buttons, links) must be minimum 44×44px.
- All `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` media query rules must disable or minimize animations.

